{Name}{}{An old mutant.}
{DescAliveShort}{}{You see an old mutant.}
{DescAliveFull}{}{You see an old mutant, resident of Broken Hills.}
{DescAliveFull}{}{When you look closely, this mutant seems very old. His muscles, however, are still strong, and his hurt pride can still be seen in his eyes.}
{Speech 1}{}{Initial preferences}
{Speech 1 Answer 2}{}{Answer}
{Speech 2}{}{I think… that… the radon gas keeps the miners young.@@I’m losing my memories… it all comes back to me… wait…@@Have you heard that the humans are plotting to kill us?@@I wish we were more accepted by the humans. We’re human in our own way.@@How goes the world outside? I don’t hear much these days.@@Someone said the FEV that made us is making us senile.@@It all seems to be slipping away from me. I used to be strong and quick... now I am little more\n than a human, it seems.@@What does life matter when it all ends anyway?@@Well… ummm… who are you?@@How do I get home?@@Didn’t I just talk to you?@@Ain’t all the humans’re doin’ this, right?}
